BASIC MCQs (1â€“10)
1. Packet filtering firewalls primarily inspect:
A. Application data
B. Packet headers
C. Encrypted payload
D. User credentials

2. Which OSI layers are mainly involved in packet filtering?
A. Application only
B. Presentation & Session
C. Network & Transport
D. Physical & Data Link

3. A Screened Host Firewall architecture consists of:
A. Single packet filter
B. Bastion host behind packet-filtering router
C. Two proxy servers
D. IDS and IPS

4. Stateful Inspection Firewall maintains information about:
A. Packet size
B. User identity
C. Active connections
D. MAC addresses

5. Which firewall type is more secure than simple packet filtering?
A. Stateless firewall
B. Packet-filtering firewall
C. Stateful inspection firewall
D. Hub

6. Next-Generation Firewalls (NGFW) differ mainly because they:
A. Are faster
B. Only filter packets
C. Provide application-level control
D. Replace routers

7. iptables is a user-space utility for managing:
A. TCP/IP stack
B. netfilter framework
C. Network drivers
D. VPN tunnels

8. Which chain handles incoming packets destined for the local system?
A. FORWARD
B. OUTPUT
C. INPUT
D. PREROUTING

9. The default policy of an iptables chain defines:
A. First rule executed
B. Action if no rule matches
C. Logging behavior
D. NAT behavior

10. Which iptables target allows packet traversal?
A. DROP
B. REJECT
C. ACCEPT
D. LOG

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11â€“20)
11. A major limitation of packet-filtering firewalls is that they:
A. Are slow
B. Cannot track session state
C. Cannot block IP addresses
D. Are complex

12. Screened host firewall improves security by:
A. Removing packet filters
B. Adding a bastion host
C. Disabling routing
D. Using encryption

13. Which table in iptables is used by default for filtering traffic?
A. nat
B. mangle
C. filter
D. raw

14. Which chain is responsible for packets generated locally?
A. INPUT
B. OUTPUT
C. FORWARD
D. POSTROUTING

15. Stateful Packet Inspection (SPI) firewall prevents attacks by:
A. Blocking all traffic
B. Tracking connection states
C. Inspecting application payload
D. Using proxy services

16. Which iptables target silently discards packets?
A. ACCEPT
B. REJECT
C. DROP
D. RETURN

17. Xtables-addons extend iptables functionality mainly by:
A. Replacing netfilter
B. Adding new matches and targets
C. Improving kernel speed
D. Removing rules

18. GeoIP blocking in iptables works by:
A. Blocking MAC addresses
B. Blocking country-based IP ranges
C. Blocking ports
D. Blocking protocols

19. Which command verifies current iptables rules?
A. iptables -A
B. iptables -F
C. iptables -L
D. iptables -X

20. IPv6 firewall rules in Linux are managed using:
A. iptables
B. nftables
C. ip6tables
D. netstat

ADVANCED MCQs (21â€“30)
21. In iptables rule processing, packets are evaluated:
A. Randomly
B. From last rule to first
C. Sequentially top to bottom
D. Based on priority value

22. If INPUT chain default policy is DROP, and no rule matches, packet is:
A. Accepted
B. Logged only
C. Dropped
D. Forwarded

23. Stateful firewall blocks spoofed packets mainly by checking:
A. TTL value
B. MAC address
C. Connection state
D. Packet size

24. Which iptables module enables stateful inspection?
A. ip_conntrack
B. ip_filter
C. ip_nat
D. ip_route

25. In SPI firewall configuration, which connection state allows return traffic?
A. NEW
B. INVALID
C. ESTABLISHED, RELATED
D. DROP

26. Internet sharing using iptables primarily requires:
A. DNS rules
B. NAT and FORWARD rules
C. INPUT rules only
D. Proxy firewall

27. Automating iptables using bash scripts is preferred because:
A. It reduces kernel load
B. Ensures rule persistence and consistency
C. Improves encryption
D. Eliminates firewalls

28. Advanced iptables setups require loading modules mainly to:
A. Improve GUI
B. Enable additional matches/targets
C. Increase bandwidth
D. Disable routing

29. Which target immediately stops rule traversal in a chain?
A. LOG
B. ACCEPT
C. DROP
D. Both B and C

30. From CCEE perspective, which statement is MOST accurate?
A. iptables is obsolete
B. Packet filtering is enough for modern threats
C. Stateful firewalls improve security without full proxy overhead
D. NGFW replaces need for iptables

